ple j b veihmeyer chairman services actuarial assurance financial  legal  tax advice management consulting revenue us billion  number of employees   website wwwkpmgcom kpmg is a professional service company and one of the big four auditors along with deloitte ernst  young ey and pricewaterhousecoopers pwc seated in amsterdam the netherlands kpmg employs  people and has three lines of services financial audit tax and advisory its tax and advisory services are further divided into various service groups the name kpmg stands for klynveld peat marwick goerdeler it was chosen when kmg klynveld main goerdeler merged with peat marwick contents  history  early years and mergers  recent history  global structure  services  community involvement and advocacy  staff  improprieties  south african complacency and corruption  kpmg tax shelter fraud  sponsorship  awards  see also  references  external links historyedit early years and mergersedit current kpmg headoffice in amstelveen the netherlands  canada square in canary wharf london the headquarters of kpmg in the uk peat marwick logo headquarters of kpmg llp the united statesbased member firm of kpmg international at  park avenue new york city the story kpmg tower on de maisonneuve boulevard in montreal the kpmg tower at  south grand avenue in los angeles kpmg offices at  west jefferson in detroit kpmg at the bay adelaide west tower in toronto the organizations history spanned three centuries in  john moxham opened a company in bristol  james grace and james grace jr bought john moaxham  co and renmed it james grace  son in   in  henry grace joined james jr and the company was renamed james  henry grace william barclay peat joined robert fletcher  co in london at  and became head of the firm in  renamed william barclay peat  co by then in  thomson mclintock founded thomson mclintock  co in glasgow in  marwick mitchell  co was founded by james marwick and roger mitchell in new york city in  ferdinand william lafrentz founded the american audit co in new york  on the other side of the atlantic in about  frank wilber main founded main  co in pittsburgh  in march  piet klijnveld and jaap kraayenhof opened an accounting firm called klynveld kraayenhof  co in amsterdam in  philipp derbyshire  gerald todd became partners in james  henry grace and it was renamed to grace darbyshire  todd  in  the american audit company was renamed fw lafrentz  co  in  william barclay peat  co and marwick mitchell  co merged to form peat marwick mitchell  company later known simply as peat marwick in  main lafrentz  co was formed by the merger of main  co and fw lafrentz  co in  grace darbyshire  todd merged with cj ryland  co to form grace ryland  co in  thomson mclintock and main lafrentz merged forming mclintock main lafrentz international  and mclintock main lafrentz international absorbed the general practice of grace ryland  co in  klynveld kraayenhof  co netherlands mclintock main lafrentz united kingdom  united states and deutsche treuhandgesellschaft germany formed kmg klynveld main goerdeler as a grouping of independent national practices to create a strong europeanbased international firm in the united states main lafrentz  co merged with hurdman and cranstoun to form main hurdman  cranstoun then in  kmg and peat marwick joined forces in the first megamerger of large accounting firms and formed a firm called kpmg in the us and most of the rest of the world and peat marwick mclintock in the uk in  the two firms settled on the common name of kpmg peat marwick mclintock but in  the firm was renamed kpmg peat marwick and in  the name was reduced again to kpmg in october  kpmg and ernst  young announced that they were to merge however while the merger to form pricewaterhousecoopers was granted regulatory approval the kpmgernst  young tieup was later abandoned recent historyedit kpmg building in kamloops british columbia in  kpmg divested its us consulting firm through an initial public offering of kpmg consulting inc which is now called bearingpoint inc in early  bearingpoint filed for chapter  bankruptcy protection the uk and dutch consulting arms were sold to atos origin in  in  kpmg divested itself of its legal arm klegal and kpmg llp sold its dispute advisory services to fti consulting kpmgs member firms in the united kingdom germany switzerland and liechtenstein merged to form kpmg europe llp in october  these member firms were followed by spain belgium the netherlands luxembourg cis azerbaijan russia ukraine belarus kyrgyzstan kazakhstan armenia and georgia turkey norway and saudi arabia they appointed joint chairmen john griffithjones and ralf nonnenmacher global structureedit each national kpmg firm is an independent legal entity and is a member of kpmg international cooperative a swiss entity registered in the swiss canton of zug kpmg international changed its legal structure from a swiss verein to a cooperative under swiss law in  this structure in which the cooperative provides support services only to the member firms is similar to other professional services networks the member firms provide the services to client the purpose is to limit the liability of each independent member michael andrew previously chairman of kpmg in australia assumed the global chairmanship in september  and is based in hong kong this is the first time a big four accounting organisation has had its global leader based in asia pacific on february   it was announced that michael andrew was retiring as chairman due to illness  and that he would be succeeded by john b veihmeyer a role he will perform alongside continuing as chairman and chief executive officer of kpmg’s us firm veihmeyer is based in new york city kpmg is registered as a multidisciplinary entity which also provides legal services servicesedit kpmg is organised into the following three service lines the  revenue shares are listed in parentheses audit  advisory  tax  tax arrangements relating to tax avoidance and multinational corporations and luxembourg which were negotiated by kpmg became public in  in the socalled luxembourg leaks community involvement and advocacyedit in march  kpmg launched a campaign designed to encourage more women to pursue careers in technologybased professions staffedit the us branch of kpmg was rated one of the top  companies for working mothers it is also ranked no  on fortune magazines  list of  best companies to work for voted for by employees kpmg was the preferred employer among the big four accounting firms according to collegegradcom it was also ranked no on the list of  best places to launch a career in  according to businessweek in  kpmg in the uk was named the best big company to work for by the times this was the fourth consecutive year that kpmg has made the top three in  in the uk kpmg introduced a programme known as flexible futures this allowed staff to volunteer to give the firm the option to either send them on a sabbatical at  pay for up to  weeks or to reduce their working hours to  days a week the option remains open to the firm until october  this facility has been invoked by the firm in some departments kpmg publicised this as innovative and an alternative approach to redundancies reaction within the firm was generally positive with over  of staff volunteering however over  staff had been made redundant prior to this announcement leading some to accuse kpmg of being hypocritical in the message that they were given in october  for the eighth year in a row kpmg was named one of canadas top  employers by mediacorp canada inc and was featured in macleans news magazine in november  kpmg was also named one of greater torontos top employers which was announced by the toronto star newspaper it was reported in early  that kpmg has about  staff in the uk and  in mainland china and hong kong kpmgs global deputy chairman predicted that headcount in china will overtake that of the uk by the end of  improprietiesedit in  kpmg agreed to pay  million and  million to settle lawsuits stemming from the firms audits of rite aid and oxford health plans inc respectively in  kpmg agreed to pay  million to settle lawsuits stemming from the collapse of software company lernout  hauspie speech products nv in  fannie mae sued kpmg for malpractice for approving years of erroneous financial statements in february  kpmg germany was investigated for ignoring questionable payments in the siemens bribery case in november  the siemens supervisory board recommended changing auditors from kpmg to ernst  young in march  kpmg was accused of enabling improper and imprudent practices at new century financial a failed mortgage company and kpmg agreed to pay  million to settle suits from xerox shareholders over manipulated earnings reports it was announced in december that two of tremont group’s rye select funds audited by kpmg had  billion invested with the madoff ponzi scheme class action suits were filed in august  it was reported by the swedish financial supervisory authority to the swedish accountancy regulator after hq bank was forced into involuntary liquidation after the financial supervisory authority revoked all its licences for breach of banking regulations in august  kpmg conducted due diligence work on hewlett packards  billion acquisition of the british software company autonomy in november  hp announced a  billion write off due to serious accounting improprieties committed by autonomy management prior to the acquisition according to an independent panel formed to investigate irregular payments made by olympus which reported in december kpmgs affiliate in japan failed in its duty to uncover fraud in april  scott london a former kpmg llp partner in charge of kpmgs us los angelesbased pacific southwest audit practice admitted passing on stock tips about clients including herbalife hlfn skechers skxn and other companies to his friend bryan shaw a california jewelrystore owner in return shaw gave london  as well as gifts that included a  rolex watch on may  shaw agreed to plead guilty to one count of conspiracy to commit securities fraud he also agreed to pay around  million in restitution and will continue to cooperate with the government as part of a plea deal with federal prosecutors this scandal led kpmg to resign as auditor for two companies in  kpmg was accused by the canada revenue agency of tax evasion schemes the cra alleges that the kpmg tax structure was in reality a sham that intended to deceive the taxman in  the canada revenue agency was found to have offered an amnesty to kpmg clients caught using an offshore taxavoidance scheme on the isle of man in  kpmg terminated five partners in its audit practice including the head of its audit practice in the united states after an investigation of advanced confidential knowledge of planned audit inspections by its regulator this followed criticism about kpmgs failure of uncovering illegal sales practices at wells fargo or potential corruption at fifa the governing international body of soccer it is reported in  that kpmg had the highest number of deficiencies among the big four cited by its regulator in the previous two years south african complacency and corruptionedit in  kpmg was found to be complicit in the corrupt business that siphoned of billions of rands hundreds of millions of usd out of the south african in collusion with the gupta family the gupta family company in the mining sector oakbay had been working with kpmg for  years prior to the revelations of corruption and collusion in  and which point kpmg decided to stop auditing oakbay the full impact and finical profit that kpmg received is yet to be determined kpmg tax shelter fraudedit main article kpmg tax shelter fraud in  irs issued summonses to kpmg for information about certain tax shelters and their investors in february  the us justice department commenced a criminal inquiry the united states member firm kpmg llp has been accused by the united states department of justice of fraud in marketing abusive tax shelters kpmg fired or forced the retirement of over a dozen who were involved kpmg llp admitted criminal wrongdoing in creating fraudulent tax shelters to help wealthy clients avoid  billion in taxes between  and  and agreed to pay  million in penalties to avoid indictment under the deferred prosecution agreement kpmg llp would not face criminal prosecution if it complied with the terms of its agreement with the government on  january  the criminal conspiracy charges against kpmg were dropped sponsorshipedit kpmg europe headquarters in the squaire building at frankfurt airport the swedish member firm was main sponsor for swedish biathlete magdalena forsberg sixtime world champion and twotime olympic medalist forsberg was working as a tax consultant at the kpmg sundsvall office parallel to her athletic career phil mickelson wearing kpmg hat in february  phil mickelson ranked one of the best golfers in the world signed a threeyear global sponsorship deal with kpmg as part of the agreement mickelson was to wear the kpmg logo on his headwear during all golf related appearances the canadian member firm sponsored alexandre bilodeau who won the first gold medal for canada on home soil in the  vancouver olympics alexandres father is a tax partner in the montreal office kpmg and mclaren technology group have formed a strategic alliance to apply mclaren applied technologies’ mat predictive analytics and technology to kpmg’s audit and advisory services mclaren  formula  car has the kpmg logo engraved above the pilot seat awardsedit no in the  worlds best outsourcing advisors – in recognition of the firms depth of experience global reach and holistic approach inducted into working mother hall of fame after being honored for  years as one of working mother magazines  best companies for working mothers international tax review asia tax awards – – in recognition of the accomplishments of kpmgs tax services and global transfer pricing services team kpmg china was awarded the  hong kong tax firm of the year and the  china transfer pricing firm of the year at the international tax reviews  asia tax awards ceremony in singapore on  november  kpmgs global transfer pricing services in china and hong kong is headed by chi cheng top  overall in consultancy rankings  by oprisk  compliance – in recognition of kpmgs experience in risk management worlds most attractive employers  – first of the big four kpmg leads all the big four professional services giant firms namely deloitte pwc and ernst  young on fortune list of  best companies to work for ranked number  in consulting magazines best firms to work for  kpmg along with pwc deloitte and pa consulting group were among the uks  top companies to work for in  see alsoedit companies portal kpmg people referencesedit  chartered accountants in england and wales a guide to historical records manchester university press  p  isbn    a b your planning resource with useful tips and techniques john wiley  p  isbn    kpmg michael andrew retiring as chairman has serious medical condition wall street journal  february  retrieved  june    a b c d kpmg  international annual review pdf retrieved  december    a b c d e f chartered accountants in england and wales a guide to historical records   a b c d e f kpmg history kpmg   a b grant julia  new york state society of certified public accountants foundation of a profession routledge p  isbn    newspaper article pittsburgh daily post pittsburgh pennsylvania  february  p  retrieved  june    family tree peat marwick mclintock iceaw  the forces of deinstiutionalisation and demise pdf retrieved  june    the development of “the big eight” accounting firms in the united states  to  accounting information retrieved  january    note kpmg derived from predecessor company founders piet klijnveld william barclay peat james marwick and reinhard goerdeler  ernst  young kpmg peat marwick to merge new company would be largest accounting 